.Dd June 29, 2026
.Dt XF-CORE 7
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm xf-core
.Nd built-in XF core module namespaces
.Sh DESCRIPTION
XF ships a built-in
.Ic core
namespace tree rather than requiring each facility to be imported from separate files.
Available namespaces observed in the source tree include:
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Ic core.math
Math functions and constants such as
.Ic pi ,
.Ic e ,
.Ic INF ,
.Ic NAN ,
and complex-number helpers.
.It Ic core.str
String manipulation helpers.
.It Ic core.os
Operating-system and filesystem helpers.
.It Ic core.ds
Data-structure helpers.
.It Ic core.regex
Regular-expression helpers.
.It Ic core.edit
Editing and text-transformation helpers.
.It Ic core.format
Formatting helpers.
.It Ic core.process
Process-management helpers.
.It Ic core.lambda
Bridge into embedded LambdaScript.
.It Ic core.byte
Bridge into embedded ByteLang.
.It Ic core.img
Image-processing helpers.
.It Ic core.generics
Generic support utilities.
.El
.Sh EMBEDDED BRIDGES
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Ic core.lambda
Provides access to LambdaScript evaluation and file execution.
.It Ic core.byte
Provides access to ByteLang check, run, or evaluation facilities.
.El
.Sh DESIGN
The core tree gives XF a broad standard environment while keeping the main language surface compact.
Core facilities are implemented in C and exposed as built-ins.
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr xf 1 ,
.Xr xf-lang 7 ,
.Xr lambdascript 7 ,
.Xr bytelang 7
